  <description type="morphology">Petiole  10--100 cm.  Blade  ovate-triangular to nearly pentagonal, 3-pinnate to 3-pinnate-pinnatifid, 30--200 × 15--100 cm; blades, rachises, and costae usually densely covered abaxially with abundant, contorted, lax, spreading hairs.  Pinnae  (proximal) triangular, distal pinnae oblong; terminal segment of each pinna ca. 4 times longer than wide, longer ultimate segments less than their width apart, ca. 1.5--5 mm wide.  Pinnules  at nearly 90° angle to costa; fertile ultimate segments adnate or equally decurrent and surcurrent.  Outer indusia  entire, pilose on margin and surface, hairs like those of axes.</description>
  <description type="habitat">In dry to moist woods and open areas in partial to full sun, forming abundant colonies</description>
